 { Historical Note } |cs|1|at|^F { @2Jacoby transfer bids were named after Oswald Jacoby of Dallas, one of @1 the greatest players in the history of the game of bridge. Jacoby first wrote about using 2@D and 2@H responses to 1NT opening bids as transfers in 1956. In 1953-54, Olle Wilner, a Swedish bridge writer and player, wrote a series of articles on the subject. It is therefore not clear that Jacoby deserves credit for the brilliant convention that bears his name. }
