|cp||at|Bridge players use the term 2-suiter (or 2-suited hand) to describe a hand that has a suit with at least 5 cards in it and another suit with at least 4 cards in it. A major 2-suiter is a 2-suited hand in which spades and hearts (the majors) are the 2 long suits.

There are a few specially designed bidding sequences that the responder to a 1NT opening bid can use to describe various types of major 2-suiters. In some cases the responder starts by bidding Stayman and in other cases he uses a Jacoby transfer bid. The strength and exact distribution of the responder's hand determine which course of action he should take.

|
