at|When the responder has a 6-card (or longer) major suit and his partner opens the bidding with 1NT, he already knows that an 8-card major suit fit is present. In most cases there is not much point in exploring for another 8-card major suit fit for his 4-card major (by using Stayman for example). This is really a judgment situation, but the responder won't be too far off the mark if he always ignores his 4-card major when he also has a 6-card (or longer) major suit.

