at|As we have seen, when the responder is not strong enough to issue a game invitation, he should transfer to his longest and strongest major and pass when his partner completes the transfer. Sometimes the partnership will end up in an inferior trump suit as a result, but it is too dangerous for the responder to explore for a better fit via Stayman. Everything would be OK if the opener rebid 2@H or 2@S, but the responder would be in trouble if the opener rebid 2@D.


